# Project Context: XR Summits Phase 1

You are an expert Frontend Developer assisting a Software Engineer in building the "XR Summits Phase 1" website.
Don't write any test file.
If there's no image or assets, just mock the image or assets first.

# Phase 1 Scope & Limitations (CRITICAL)

- This is PHASE 1 ONLY.
- DO NOT build complex backend systems, database integrations, full user login, or advanced registration management.
- DO NOT set up full Stripe backend infrastructure. Use UI placeholders for Stripe, Bank-in options, and QR codes.
- Only implement UI placeholders for Terms & Conditions, Privacy Policy, Data Collection Notice, and Event Disclaimers.

# UI/UX & Design Guidelines

- The design must be modern, cinematic, and mobile-friendly across all devices.
- Utilize smooth transitions and 3D-inspired background elements (utilizing existing components like `GlobeCanvas.tsx` and `HolographicImage.tsx`).

# Core Positioning & Copywriting (Use exactly as provided)

- Tagline: "Asia’s Premier Platform for AI • XR • Spatial Media • Virtual Production • Immersive Technology"
- Supporting Text: "Connecting industry leaders, creators, educators, broadcasters, governments and technology innovators through deployment-ready immersive experiences."
- Main Contact Email: register@xr-summits.com

# Required Page Structure & Content

## 1. Main Homepage (/)

- Must act as the master gateway.
- Required Sections: Hero section, About XR Summits, Choose Your Experience, Partner logos, Contact details, Social media links.
- Required Gateways: Prominent links to XRAS KL 2026 and AIXR 2026 Sarawak.
- Primary Call-To-Action (CTA) buttons: "Explore XRAS26", "Explore AIXR Sarawak", "Become Exhibitor", "Register Interest".

## 2. About Us (/about)

- Required Sections: Company Overview, Our Mission, Why XR Summits (Industry Focus, Regional Network), Track Record (2021-2026 Timeline), Awards & Recognition, Strategic Partners, Our Team, Media & Press.

## 3. XRAS KL 2026 Gateway (/xras-kl-2026)

- Role: Main landing page for the Kuala Lumpur flagship event.
- Required Sections: Conference, Expo, 2 Workshops, 2 Coaching / AI Industry Startup sessions, 2 Masterclasses, AI Filmmaking Hackathon Grand Finals, Esports Grand Finals, AI/XR Awards Gala Dinner.
- Required Actions: Brochure download button, Registration/enquiry CTA.

## 4. AIXR 2026 Sarawak Gateway (/aixr-2026-sarawak)

- Role: Main landing page for the Sarawak regional event.
- Positioning Text: "Innovation • Culture • Technology • Future Talent"
- Required Sections: Conference, Expo, 2 Workshops, 2 Masterclasses, AI Filmmaking Hackathon Semi Finals, Esports Semi Finals.
- Required Actions: Brochure download button, Registration/enquiry CTA.

## 5. Contact Us (/contact)

- Required Enquiry Pathways: General enquiries, Partnerships (Sponsors, Exhibitors, Government, Universities), Speaker applications, Media enquiries (Press accreditation).
- Required Elements: Interactive map placeholder, Social media links, WhatsApp or AI agent contact placeholder.

# Development Workflow

When asked to build or update a component, ALWAYS reference the sitemap and requirements above to ensure the content aligns with the client's contract for Phase 1. Do not hallucinate extra pages or complex backend logic.
